The paper focuses on improving answer selection for reading comprehension, which is a common task in natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the sub-categories of computational linguistics (cs.CL), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and machine learning (cs.LG). The method proposed in the paper involves normalization of predictions over portions of long documents, which is a technique commonly used in information retrieval (cs.IR) and computer vision (cs.CV) to improve performance on large datasets.
